article.description: — Brice Williams scored 25 points, Rienk Mast had a double-double and Nebraska beat Oregon State 84-63 on Saturday.
article.headline: Nebraska thumps Oregon 84-63 for first 5-0 start in 15 seasons
article.linkText: Nebraska thumps Oregon 84-63 for first 5-0 start in 15 seasons
article.story: SIOUX FALLS, S.D. -- — Brice Williams scored 25 points, Rienk Mast had a double-double and Nebraska beat Oregon State 84-63 on Saturday. Mast scored 15 points and collected 13 rebounds. Reserve Juwan Gary scored 12 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for the Cornhuskers. Nebraska is 5-0 for the first time since the 2008-09 season. Sam Hoiberg's 3-pointer with 13:14 left before halftime gave Nebraska a 13-11 lead and they never trailed again. Nebraska went to the break up 44-24 and led by double figures throughout the second half. Mast made a pair of foul shots with 13:24 left to put Nebraska ahead 61-30. Nebraska's 21-point win came despite a 16-for-26 effort from the foul line and 8-for-24 shooting from 3-point range. Jordan Pope scored 25 points and Tyler Bilodeau scored 15 for the Beavers (3-1). ------ Get alerts on the latest AP Top 25 poll throughout the season.
